  "prompt": "Is money laundering subject to legal prosecution?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is subject to legal prosecution under both Chinese law and the laws of many other countries. In China, money laundering is considered a serious criminal offense and is strictly prohibited. The **Anti-Money Laundering Law of the People's Republic of China** and the **Criminal Law of the People's Republic of China** both have specific provisions targeting money laundering activities.\n\n### Key Legal Provisions in China:\n1. **Anti-Money Laundering Law (2007, amended in 2021):**  \n   - This law requires financial institutions and specific non-financial institutions to establish anti-money laundering mechanisms, including customer due diligence, record-keeping, and reporting of suspicious transactions.  \n   - Violations can result in administrative penalties, fines, and even criminal liability.  \n\n2. **Criminal Law (Article 191):**  \n   - Money laundering is explicitly criminalized under Article 191.  \n   - Penalties include imprisonment, fines, and confiscation of illegal proceeds.  \n\n3. **International Cooperation:**  \n   China actively participates in global anti-money laundering efforts and collaborates with international organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) to combat money laundering and terrorist financing.  \n\n### Examples of Money Laundering Activities:\n- Concealing the source of illegally obtained funds through complex financial transactions.  \n- Using legitimate businesses to disguise illegal proceeds.  \n- Transferring illicit funds across borders to evade detection.  \n\n### Enforcement:\nChina has established dedicated agencies, such as the **China Anti-Money Laundering Monitoring and Analysis Center** (CAMLMAC), and works closely with financial regulators and law enforcement to detect, investigate, and prosecute money laundering cases.  \n\nIn summary, money laundering is a serious crime in China, and those involved in such activities will face severe legal consequences, including criminal prosecution, heavy fines, and imprisonment.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
